{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The region is engaged in a war over coal, with miners and their families pitted against environmental activists.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by author Jason Howard warns that residents of Appalachia are engaged in a heated debate over coal, particularly mountaintop removal mining, with miners and their families pitted against environmental activists; notes that the coal industry has succeeded in demonizing the environmentalists by saying regulation threatens jobs; calls on industry leaders and their elected allies to stop their propaganda and engage in an honest, civil dialogue about the health and environmental risks.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "19", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Jason", "role": "reported", "lastname": "HOWARD", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By JASON HOWARD", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/09/opinion/appalachia-turns-on-itself.html", "lead_paragraph": "The region is engaged in a war over coal, with miners and their families pitted against environmental activists.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Appalachia Turns on Itself", "seo": "Appalachia Turns on Itself", "main": "Appalachia Turns on Itself", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor", "kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor"}, "_id": "53f8959338f0d835538dccf4", "word_count": "708", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2012/07/09/opinion/0709OPEDbavarsky-1341617008983/0709OPEDbavarsky-1341617008983-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2012/07/09/opinion/0709OPEDbavarsky-1341617008983/0709OPEDbavarsky-1341617008983-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 390, "url": "images/2012/07/09/opinion/0709OPEDbavarsky-1341617008983/0709OPEDbavarsky-1341617008983-articleLarge-v3.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2012/07/09/opinion/0709OPEDbavarsky-1341617008983/0709OPEDbavarsky-134161700